{"questionId":"27683","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math> be the complex number defined as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>z</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mtext>i </mtext></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℕ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo> </mo><msub><mi>w</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>…</mo><msub><mi>z</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mi>z</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo> </mo></math>&nbsp;for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℕ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence or otherwise, show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>arg</mtext><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>w</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mtext>arctan</mtext><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>arg</mtext><mfenced><msub><mi>w</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mtext>arg</mtext><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mtext>arg</mtext><mfenced><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mtext>arg</mtext><mfenced><msub><mi>z</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://